<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 08 at 11:18PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Armstrong and southern Donley Counties through 1215 AM CDT...
At 1118 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles northwest of Brice, or 16 miles southwest of Clarendon, moving
east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern
Armstrong and southern Donley Counties.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
